[:fineness by metric:]

- Given a set $$X$$ with two [[metric]]s $$d_1$$ and $$d_2$$, inducing topologies $$\mathcal T_1$$ and $$\mathcal T_2$$, [[TFAE]]:
    - $$\mathcal T_2$$ is [finer]([[fineness]]) than $$\mathcal T_1$$
    - for every $$x \in X$$ and $$\varepsilon > 0$$ we have some $$\delta > 0$$ where $$B_{d_2}(x, \delta) \subseteq B_{d_1}(x, \varepsilon)$$
        - Lemma 20.2 in [[JRM:Top.2]]
